SBM Solar Inc. has developed proprietary non-glass technology, and a process to make customizable PV modules that are lightweight and have a low glare surface. SBM Solar Inc. dedicates itself to be the pioneer of the solar field for non glass PV module manufacturing. Description: A company that's dedicated to identify and import the highest-quality matcha available and provide the world’s best matcha tea.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Stone ground matcha tea, sourced directly from the farm. We are a group of friends who share a common love of Japanese culture and high-quality tea and do our best to make lifestyle choices that promote optimum health. We have long been impressed by the solid body of scientific evidence for the health benefits of tea – matcha green tea in particular. This special beverage is unlike any other green tea. Superior Japanese matcha looks and tastes great - brilliantly green, sweet, with a rich, complex and satisfying flavor. Our first sip. On a fateful trip to Japan, we first tasted this wonderful emerald green elixir. We liked matcha so much that we wanted to recreate the experience at home and drink it regularly. At first, we had to bring small tins of it back from Japan, because it was not available here. We also brought back tea bowls and bamboo measuring scoops and whisks. Soon we were in the habit of drinking a morning bowl of matcha and turning friends onto it. Gradually, we learned more about this rare and highly prized form of green tea: how it is cultivated and processed, the distinction among different grades, how to recognize the best matcha. We've become so excited about the unique and amazing benefits of matcha we decided to form a company to identify, import, and provide really great matcha tea!

Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Superfecta began in 2001 as “Superfecta Recordings” a record label focused on reissuing out-of-print titles from ‘80s alternative artists. Since there are only so many people who want a remastered “Long Live the New Flesh”, the company evolved into an online store called “The Ideal Copy”. In 2005, founder Jason Fiber was recruited by Jac Holzman and The Warner Music Group to found and launch the first “online” record label called Cordless Recordings, where he signed the Boston-based synthpop band Freezepop. After the label merged with another company Fiber departed and was asked by Freezepop to manage them. After a bit of convincing he founded the management/booking/consulting company known today as Superfecta Entertainment. Superfecta has produced several successful tours, including multiple world tours (including several runs for Combichrist as support for Rammstein) as well as three Brazilian tours for Information Society. Superfecta specializes in taking small, but motivated, artists and growing their careers. Moving away from strictly music, Superfecta has recently started managing the well known tattoo artist/model Megan Massacre. Their next moves are focused on continuing to discover more talent of this caliber, expanding their business to encapsulate their unique approach.

It also provides searchable lessons, explanations, problems, solutions, and quizzes for math subjects. Among its many homework help and self-study guides for middle and high school students is NutshellMath, an online service that provides interactive math explanations and multimedia demonstrations of math concepts. Academy123 was founded by Maury Friedman and Yarone Goren in January 2004 and is based in Westlake Village, California. Description: VTap is a video search engine designed for broadband-enabled phones.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Vtap is a mobile search service that's fine-tuned for video but can be used for audio and text as well.   The technology provides relevant video results by indexing video metadata, like tags and surrounding text, instead of actual video file innards. When users start typing search keywords into the query box, the search engine speedily starts returning relevant results based on the letters they have already started typing. Vtap can do this because their search technology indexes letters and characters instead of whole words like other search engines. This allows users to type in abbreviated search keywords instead of typing a whole word, which makes more sense for mobile users. They plan on launching the service in September 2007. Mobile video search competitors include [MyWaves](http://mywaves.com) and [blueapple.mobi](http://www.blueapple.mobi/).
Industry Groups: Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Software, Video
